19/09/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The United States stands with Turkey and supports government efforts against the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK), US Undersecretary of State for Political Affairs Nicholas Burns said on Tuesday (September 18th) as he arrived for a two-day visit to Ankara. Burns added that the US wants to see Turkey live in peace. At a press conference, he also expressed Washington's support for Ankara's EU membership bid.
In other news Tuesday, Turkish military forces began a broad-scale operation against PKK militants in the Sirnak, Siirt and Hakkari provinces in the southeast. Cobra and Super Cobra helicopters will be used in the operation, which includes 10,000 troops. (Cihan - 19/09/07; Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency, KUNA - 18/09/07)
